Under the new guidelines, airlines whose planes are adequately protected from electronic interference could allow passengers to use these devices during take-off, landing and steering, the FAA said.
Most new airliners and other aircraft modified so that passengers can use Wi-Fi at high altitudes are expected to meet these criteria.
