He said it was meant to prevent evidence from being corrupted, but it was “overdone” and poorly implemented.
The New South Wales YMCA was not a child-friendly organization during Jonathan Lord’s tenure between 2009 and 2011, Professor Stephen Smallbone of Griffith University, an expert on child molestation, told the commission.
